        role: "Afghan President (2001–2014) — America's man in Kabul",
        side: "belligerent",
        importance: 78,
        portrait: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/84/Hamid_Karzai_December_2017.jpg",
        note: "Charming, well-dressed, and fluent in English — perfect for TV interviews, less perfect for governing a country where most people had never seen a TV. Tolerated warlords because he needed them. Took CIA cash because everyone did. Grew increasingly critical of the US as the war dragged on. Now lives in Taliban-controlled Kabul, occasionally commenting on politics. The man America installed outlasted America's interest in the country.",
