        side: "belligerent",
        importance: 88,
        portrait: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e4/Nasser_portrait2.jpg",
        note: "The most charismatic Arab leader of the century. Built a movement on pan-Arab nationalism and defiance of the West. Closed the Straits of Tiran because he needed a political win after Yemen. Israel called the bluff. Nasser wasn't ready for war. His army wasn't ready for war. His air force wasn't ready for anything — it was parked in rows on open runways on the morning Israel attacked. Nasser offered to resign after the defeat. Egypt refused. He died three years later, at 52. The defeat killed the dream of pan-Arabism. It may have killed him too.",
