        portrait: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4f/Golda_Meir_%281978%29.jpg",
        note: "Received intelligence warnings before the war. Chose not to preemptively strike (fearing international backlash) and not to fully mobilize (fearing economic cost). Both decisions nearly proved fatal. Led Israel through its darkest hours since 1948. Reportedly authorized nuclear weapons preparation on Day 2. Resigned in 1974 after the Agranat Commission exposed the intelligence failures. The woman who held Israel together during the crisis was the same woman whose decisions helped create it. Leadership is complicated.",
