        portrait: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a1/Sheikh_Mujibur_Rahman_in_1950.jpg",
        note: "Won the 1970 election. Arrested on the night of Operation Searchlight. Spent the entire war in a Pakistani prison — reportedly with a grave dug outside his cell. Released after Pakistan's surrender. Returned to lead Bangladesh. **Assassinated** in a military coup on **August 15, 1975** — along with most of his family. His daughter, **Sheikh Hasina**, survived (she was abroad) and later became prime minister. The father of Bangladesh was killed by Bangladeshis. The nation he created has never been stable enough to properly mourn him.",
