        note: "Charismatic, ruthless, and Israel's chosen candidate — Gemayel united the Christian militias through force (including killing rival Christian leaders) and was elected president in **August 1982** with Israeli backing. **Assassinated** on September 14, 1982 — two weeks before taking office. His death triggered the **Sabra and Shatila massacre** (Phalangist revenge against Palestinians). The man who was supposed to end the war was killed before he could start his presidency. His brother Amine took over. The war continued for eight more years.",
