        portrait: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c9/%C3%81lvaro_Uribe.jpg",
        note: "Launched the US-backed military offensive that weakened FARC to the point of negotiation — but then **opposed the 2016 peace deal**, leading the 'No' campaign in the referendum. Uribe's position: FARC should be defeated, not negotiated with. His critics' response: Uribe's father was killed by FARC, his allies included paramilitaries, and his 'democratic security' policy produced the false positives scandal. The most effective wartime president opposed the peace his war made possible. Colombia's politics are like its conflict: nobody is entirely right, and nobody is entirely wrong.",
