        role: "Head of State of Nigeria — the man who won the war and chose mercy over revenge",
        side: "belligerent",
        importance: 92,
        portrait: "/portraits/placeholder-figure.svg",
        note: "Young (32 at the war's start), Christian (from the Middle Belt), and genuinely committed to Nigerian unity. His 'no victor, no vanquished' policy was one of post-colonial Africa's most remarkable acts — preventing the reprisals that post-war logic demanded. Gowon chose reconciliation over punishment. He authorized the blockade that starved millions. He also prevented the massacre that could have followed the victory. History judges him on both. The mercy was real. So was the famine.",
