        portrait: "/portraits/placeholder-figure.svg",
        note: "Born into a relatively prosperous family. Studied in Paris where he absorbed Maoism and developed a vision of agrarian revolution that made Mao look moderate. Led the Khmer Rouge from the jungle, kept his identity secret even from most of his followers ('Angkar' was everything; individuals were nothing), and after victory implemented the most radical social experiment in history: emptied cities, abolished money, eliminated intellectuals, and worked the population to death in rice paddies. **1.5–2 million** died. Vietnam overthrew him in 1979. He fought on as a guerrilla until 1997. **Died** in April 1998 — reportedly after being told he'd be handed to an international tribunal. He was never tried. The man who killed 25% of his country died in a jungle hut, unpunished.",
