        note: "Medical student turned guerrilla fighter — led the TPLF from the Tigrayan mountains to power in Addis Ababa. As prime minister (1995–2012), he created **ethnic federalism**, presided over rapid economic growth, and became increasingly authoritarian — suppressing dissent, jailing journalists, and rigging elections. Died in office in 2012. His ethnic federal system — designed to prevent the centralized tyranny of the Derg — instead institutionalized ethnic politics in a way that led directly to the **2020 Tigray War**. The architect of post-war Ethiopia built a structure that collapsed a decade after his death.",
