        importance: 92,
        portrait: "/portraits/placeholder-figure.svg",
        note: "Military dictator who'd seized power in 1969 and aligned Somalia with the Soviet Union. Launched the Ogaden invasion to fulfill **Greater Somalia** — the dream of uniting all Somali-inhabited territories. The invasion's initial success was intoxicating: ~90% of the Ogaden captured in weeks. Then the Soviets switched sides and the dream became a nightmare. The defeat didn't just end the Ogaden campaign — it began the destruction of the Somali state. Barre was overthrown in **1991**. Somalia hasn't had a functional central government since. The man who wanted a Greater Somalia produced a Lesser Somalia — fragmented, failed, and perpetually at war with itself.",
