        role: "The former Gaddafi general who tried to become Libya's new strongman — and got closer than anyone expected",
        side: "belligerent",
        importance: 80,
        portrait: "/portraits/placeholder-figure.svg",
        note: "A former **Gaddafi general** who'd been captured in the Chad war (1987), defected, spent 20 years in **Virginia** (near CIA headquarters — coincidence or not), and returned to Libya during the 2011 revolution. Haftar played a minor role in the first civil war but became the **dominant military figure** in the second (2014–2020) — commanding the **Libyan National Army** (LNA) from eastern Libya with backing from **Russia** (Wagner Group mercenaries), **UAE**, **Egypt**, and **France**. He launched an offensive on Tripoli in 2019 that nearly succeeded before Turkish intervention stopped it. Haftar is the strongman who wants to be Gaddafi's successor — minus the tent and the Green Book. Libya's future: probably more war, possibly Haftar, definitely no peace.",
