        note: "A **Marine lieutenant colonel** on the National Security Council staff who orchestrated the secret network that sold weapons to Iran and diverted the profits to the Contras — in direct violation of the Boland Amendment. North shredded documents, lied to Congress, and became the **face of Iran-Contra** during televised hearings where he appeared in uniform, invoked patriotism, and became a **conservative folk hero**. Convicted of three felonies (overturned on technicality due to immunized Congressional testimony). Later ran for US Senate (lost), became a Fox News commentator, and served as president of the NRA. The man who broke American law to fund a proxy war became a television celebrity. In America, breaking the law for the right ideological reasons is a career move.",
