        portrait: "/portraits/placeholder-figure.svg",
        note: "**Min Aung Hlaing** ordered the 2017 'clearance operations' that the UN concluded constituted genocide. He has never acknowledged wrongdoing. He has never been held accountable. In **February 2021**, he led a **military coup** — overthrowing the elected government (including Suu Kyi) and plunging Myanmar into civil war. He is now the head of state of a country that is simultaneously committing genocide against the Rohingya, fighting a civil war against its own population, and collapsing economically. He is sanctioned by the US, EU, and UK. He is wanted by the ICC. He is still in power. The gap between 'wanted for genocide' and 'running a country' is the gap between international law and international reality.",
