        note: "The **most dramatic moral fall** in modern political history. **Suu Kyi** spent **15 years under house arrest** for opposing Myanmar's military dictatorship. She won the **Nobel Peace Prize** in 1991. She was the world's most famous political prisoner, mentioned in the same breath as Mandela and Gandhi. Then she became Myanmar's de facto leader in 2016 — and when the military committed genocide against the Rohingya, she **defended it**. At the ICJ in December 2019, she argued the military used 'disproportionate force' but denied genocide. Her defenders say she was constrained by the constitution (the military controlled defense). Her critics say she chose complicity — and that her silence during the 2017 operations, when she could have spoken out, was a moral choice. After the 2021 coup, the military she defended **imprisoned her** — sentenced to 27 years on charges widely seen as politically motivated. She is now in prison, put there by the same generals whose genocide she defended. The irony is Shakespearean. The tragedy is real.",
