        portrait: "/portraits/placeholder-figure.svg",
        note: "**Min Aung Hlaing** is the common thread connecting Myanmar's worst atrocities: he ordered the **Rohingya genocide** (2017), staged the **2021 coup**, and now presides over a war that is destroying the country. He is **ICC-investigated** for the Rohingya genocide, **sanctioned** by the US, EU, and others, and **internationally isolated** — but still in power, still commanding airstrikes on villages, and still refusing to negotiate. His coup was motivated by personal ambition (avoiding retirement) and institutional arrogance (the military's belief that it owns Myanmar). The result: a war he's losing, an economy he's destroyed, and a country that hates him. He will likely end his career either in exile, in prison, or in a grave. The question is how many more people he'll kill before one of those outcomes arrives.",
