        note: "**Duwa Lashi La** — a **Kachin** leader and former NLD lawmaker — serves as acting president of the **NUG**, the parallel government that organizes the resistance. His appointment was symbolically important: a member of an **ethnic minority** leading a government that had historically been Bamar-dominated. He declared the **'people's defensive war'** in September 2021 — the moment the revolution officially became an armed conflict. The NUG operates from undisclosed locations (partly in exile, partly inside Myanmar), coordinates with ethnic armed organizations, and attempts to govern liberated areas. It's a government without a capital, without a treasury, and without international recognition (no country has formally recognized the NUG). But it's the closest thing to a legitimate government Myanmar has — elected lawmakers organizing resistance against a military that stole power. Duwa Lashi La's role is more symbolic than operational, but symbols matter in a revolution.",
